page.title: 10LAND COVER,LICKEY/CATSHILL
page.content: Many birds fly over : Canada geese, swans from Europe,sparrow hawks, kestrels,woodpeckers and owls. We have many species of animals in our woods:hares,yellow brimstone butterflies,badgers,hedgehogs,foxes, frogs,dragonflies,mice,rabbits,insects bees and ants.We have found footprints and droppings of hares and badgers. {Armed Forces The RAF are the most frequent visitors .Our survey showed that about 50% of people noticed the planes and didn't mind ,40% hadn't noticed them and 10% didn't like the noise and how low they flew.People liked seeing the RAF flying over, knew that practice somewhere was necessary and felt safer with the knowledge that the RAF are protecting them. In 1982, at the time of the Falklands dispute, aerial activity increased.
